# Browser & game testing (IDE)

The user expects agents to **run automated tests and drive browsers** from this workspace ‚Äî not only suggest manual steps.

## Development workflow (layered gates)

Match CI job order. Use **IDE test runners** while iterating, **headless before ship**:

```
edit code
  ‚Üí Testing sidebar: Vitest / Playwright (or npm run check)
  ‚Üí npm run check              (quality: lint + tsc + vitest + build)
  ‚Üí npm run test:e2e:headed    (or :ui ‚Äî show browser; UI / player-flow changes)
  ‚Üí npm run test:e2e           (headless re-run; confirm CI e2e job)
  ‚Üí npm run test:e2e:cross     (pre-PR when clicks, keyboard nav, CSS, or e2e touched)
  ‚Üí PR ‚Üí CI runs quality + e2e + e2e-cross
```

Install extensions once: `npm run setup:extensions` (see `DEV.md`). Vitest + Playwright integrate with the Testing sidebar.

| Stage | Command | Purpose |
|-------|---------|---------|
| 1 ‚Äî Fast | `npm run check` | Logic, types, build; blocks bad merges early |
| 2 ‚Äî Show | `test:e2e:headed` or `:ui` | User + agent watch title ‚Üí arena; catch flow breaks |
| 3 ‚Äî CI smoke | `test:e2e` | Headless Chromium; same as CI `e2e` job |
| 4 ‚Äî CI cross | `test:e2e:cross` | Firefox + WebKit; same as CI `e2e-cross` job |
| Gap fill | `npm run dev` + browser MCP | Flows not yet in `e2e/` (e.g. full combat loop) |

**Docs-only** ‚Äî skip tests. **Pure logic** ‚Äî stage 1 is enough; add `tests/*.test.js` when touching algorithms.

Playwright starts its own Vite `webServer` ‚Äî no `npm run dev` needed for e2e.

## Agent obligation

After substantive changes, **run the matching stage(s) in the terminal** and fix failures before reporting done. Do not end with ‚Äúyou should run tests‚Äù unless blocked.

- UI / navigation / HUD ‚Üí run **stage 2** (`:headed` or `:ui`) so Playwright is visible.
- Before suggesting merge or opening a PR ‚Üí run **stages 1 + 3**; add **stage 4** for UI/e2e work.
- Report what ran and pass/fail counts in the task summary.

## What smoke e2e proves (and does not)

**Covers today:** title boot, canvas, play ‚Üí arena HUD, village hub, dev level-up, dev panel, daily challenge label, skill tree, quest board, arena pause/resume, seeded URL without page errors.

**Does not cover:** full combat balance QA, horde perf at max cap, mobile layout on real devices, itch/Pages deploy smoke. Green e2e = **core path intact**, not full game QA.

## E2e conventions (from this repo)

- **Readiness first** ‚Äî app sets `<html data-game-ready="title|arena-hud|village">` (`src/lib/gameReady.js`); use `e2e/helpers/gameReady.ts` (`waitForGameReady`) instead of long blind timeouts.
- **Helpers first** ‚Äî reuse `navigation.ts` (`gotoClean`), `gameFlow.ts` (`startQuickArena`, `openSkillTreeViaDev`, `pauseArenaAndResume`); extend helpers before duplicating steps.
- **Stable selectors** ‚Äî `#btn-play`, `#btn-confirm`, `#hp-bar`, HUD ids; `getByRole` for headings.
- **Navigation** ‚Äî `goto(..., { waitUntil: 'commit' })` then readiness/visibility asserts; avoid waiting for all assets on WebGL SPAs.
- **Visibility over timing** ‚Äî `toBeVisible()` / `waitForGameReady`; avoid bare `waitForTimeout`.
- **Keyboard-nav / WebKit clicks** ‚Äî if Playwright click is blocked, use DOM click in helper (see `startQuickArena` `evaluate` pattern); document in helper comment.
- **Fresh save** ‚Äî `gotoClean` clears `localStorage` before each test.
- **New regression** ‚Äî player-visible bug fix or new menu flow ‚Üí add/extend spec + run stage 2.

Specs: `e2e/smoke.spec.ts` (Chromium / `test:e2e`), `e2e/cross-browser.spec.ts` (Firefox + WebKit / `test:e2e:cross`). Config: `playwright.config.ts` (`testMatch` split; `workers: 1` when `CROSS_BROWSER=1`).

## Firefox / WebKit on Linux CI (WebGL)

GigaZonk uses Three.js WebGL. **Firefox headless on Linux does not support WebGL** ([Mozilla #1375585](https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=1375585); [Playwright #13146](https://github.com/microsoft/playwright/issues/13146)).

CI `e2e-cross` job:

- Installs **Xvfb**
- Runs `xvfb-run --auto-servernum -- npm run test:e2e:cross`
- Playwright sets **headed** Firefox/WebKit when `CI` + `CROSS_BROWSER` (see `playwright.config.ts`)

`firefoxUserPrefs` alone is not sufficient. Boot optimizations (`Game.js` lazy arena, readiness markers) reduce flake but do not replace Xvfb.

## Flake triage

1. Re-run failing spec headless: `npm run test:e2e -- e2e/smoke.spec.ts`
2. Cross-browser timeout ‚Üí run `test:e2e:cross` alone (sequential workers); confirm `data-game-ready` in trace
3. Firefox CI only ‚Üí verify Xvfb + headed in `.github/workflows/ci.yml` and `playwright.config.ts`
4. WebKit click failures ‚Üí check keyboard-nav guard; prefer helper DOM click
5. Still flaky ‚Üí `:ui` trace on failing step; tighten readiness wait or selector

Cross-browser failures write `test-results/browser-errors/{browser}.json` ‚Äî read before guessing.

## Playwright commands

```bash
npm run test:e2e           # headless ‚Äî CI parity (stage 3)
npm run test:e2e:headed      # visible browser (stage 2)
npm run test:e2e:ui          # step-through inspector (stage 2)
npm run test:e2e:cross       # all browsers (stage 4)
```

## When to use each tool

| Need | Tool |
|------|------|
| Regression / CI | Playwright headless (stage 3) |
| Unit logic | Vitest Explorer or `npm run test` |
| Agent session ‚Äî show browser | Playwright `--headed` or `--ui` (stage 2) |
| Firefox + Safari | `test:e2e:cross` (stage 4) |
| Flow not in e2e yet | `npm run dev` + cursor-ide-browser MCP |
| Agent write-then-verify | Playwright MCP (`setup:mcp`) |
| Three.js scene asserts | `@timjen/playwright-three` + `e2e/helpers/playwrightThree.ts` |
| Console / localStorage (dev running) | vite-mcp `http://localhost:5173/__mcp` |
| Chrome traces / Lighthouse | chrome-devtools-mcp |
| Library docs (agent) | context7 MCP |
| Quick peek in editor | Simple Browser ‚Üí `http://localhost:5173` |
| Balance JSON | JSON Crack extension on `data/*.json` |
| Structured in-game errors | `window.__gigazonkErrors.exportJson()` in dev |
| Dev game API (e2e / debug) | `window.__gigazonkGame` in dev (`src/main.js`) |

### chrome-devtools-mcp vs cursor-ide-browser

- **Playwright** ‚Äî repeatable regression; only tool that runs Firefox + WebKit in CI.
- **Playwright MCP** ‚Äî agent-driven browser verify (`@playwright/mcp` via `npm run setup:mcp`).
- **playwright-three** ‚Äî scene/object asserts when DOM selectors are not enough (`window.PLAYWRIGHT_THREE.scene`).
- **cursor-ide-browser** ‚Äî exploratory click-through when no spec exists yet.
- **vite-mcp** ‚Äî dev server console + `localStorage` without extra browser.
- **chrome-devtools-mcp** ‚Äî network, perf traces, source-mapped stacks.

## Manual / MCP checklist (gaps only)

1. `npm run dev` ‚Üí `http://localhost:5173`
2. `browser_navigate` ‚Üí snapshot before clicks ‚Üí screenshot after state change
3. URL flags: `?dev=1`, `?seed=42`, `?biome=frost`, `?coins=500` (see `DEV.md`)

Production build smoke: `npm run build && npm run preview` (base `/gigazonk/`).

## CI parity

`.github/workflows/ci.yml`: `quality` ‚Üí `e2e` + `e2e-cross` in parallel. `e2e-cross` uses **Xvfb + headed** for WebGL. Local pre-push gate:

```bash
npm run check && npm run test:e2e && npm run test:e2e:cross
```
